The settlers made their own sugar and sirup from the maple trees of which there was a great number in the forests. As late as 1860 the pioneers made large amounts. In 1858, 8,300 pounds were made the value of which was $584. The other farm products of 1850 in Crawford county were: Wheat, 19,950 bushels; corn, 195,690 bushels; butter, 34,445 pounds;
